default: 1000)\n36:   - [ ] `WorkloadManagerURL string` - Workload manager endpoint\n37:   - [ ] `AgentcubeNamespace string` - Router namespace (default: \"default\")\n38: - [ ] Implement `DefaultConfig()` function returning default configuration\n39: - [ ] Implement `LoadConfig() error` function to load from environment variables\n40: - [ ] Add validation logic for required configuration fields\n41: - [ ] Create `config_test.go` with unit tests for configuration loading\n42:   - [ ] `TestDefaultConfig`\n43:   - [ ] `TestLoadConfigFromEnv`\n44:   - [ ] `TestConfigValidation`\n45:   - [ ] `TestMissingRequiredConfig`\n46: \n47: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig` to ensure configuration handling works correctly\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Task 3: Implement common types and data structures\n52: - [ ] Create `pkg/router/types.go`\n53: - [ ] Define `SandboxInfo` struct with all required fields\n54:   - [ ] `Kind string` - \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n55:   - [ ] `SandboxID string` - Unique identifier\n56:   - [ ] `SandboxName string` - Pod name\n57:   - [ ] `SandboxNamespace string` - Pod namespace\n58:   - [ ] `Name string` - Resource name\n59:   - [ ] `EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint` - Service endpoints\n60:   - [ ] `SessionID string` - Session identifier\n61:   - [ ] `CreatedAt time.Time` - Creation timestamp\n62:   - [ ] `ExpiresAt time.Time` - Expiration timestamp\n63:   - [ ] `Status string` - Sandbox status\n64:   - [ ] `PodIP string` - Pod IP address\n65:   - [ ] `WorkloadName string` - Workload name\n66:   - [ ] `Namespace string` - Resource namespace\n67:   - [ ] `LastActivityAt time.Time` - Last activity timestamp\n68: - [ ] Define `SandboxEntryPoint` struct\n69:   - [ ] `Path string` - URL path prefix\n70:   - [ ] `Protocol string` - \"http\" or \"https\"\n71:   - [ ] `Endpoint string` - Target URL endpoint\n72: - [ ] Define `ErrorResponse` struct\n73:   - [ ] `Error string` - Error message\n74:   - [ ] `Code string` - Error code (optional)\n75: - [ ] Define `JWTClaims` struct\n76:   - [ ] `SessionID string`\n77:   - [ ] `jwt.RegisteredClaims`\n78: - [ ] Add JSON tags for all struct fields\n79: - [ ] Create `types_test.go` with struct validation tests\n80:   - [ ] `TestSandboxInfoJSONSerialization`\n81:   - [ ] `TestErrorResponseJSONSerialization`\n82:   - [ ] `TestSandboxEntryPointValidation`\n83: \n84: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestTypes` and verify JSON serialization works correctly\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Task 4: Implement JWT manager for authentication\n89: - [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n90: - [ ] Define `JWTManager` struct\n91:   - [ ] `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n92:   - [ ] `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n93:   - [ ] `clientset kubernetes.Interface`\n94:   - [ ] `namespace string`\n95: - [ ] Implement `NewJWTManager()` constructor function\n96: - [ ] Implement `GenerateToken()` method\n97:   - [ ] Create JWT claims with session ID\n98:   - [ ] Set token expiration (5 minutes)\n99:   - [ ] Sign token with RSA private key\n100:   - [ ] Return signed token string\n101: - [ ] Implement `ValidateToken()` method\n102:   - [ ] Parse and verify token signature\n103:   - [ ] Extract session ID from claims\n104:   - [ ] Validate token expiration\n105:   - [ ] Return session ID or error\n106: - [ ] Implement `generateRSAKeyPair()` private method\n107:   - [ ] Generate 2048-bit RSA key pair\n108:   - [ ] Return private and public keys\n109: - [ ] Implement `storeOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` method\n110:   - [ ] Check for existing Kubernetes secret\n111:   - [ ] Load keys from secret if exists\n112:   - [ ] Generate and store new keys if not exists\n113: - [ ] Implement `storeJWTKeySecret()` private method\n114:   - [ ] Create/update Kubernetes secret\n115:   - [ ] Store RSA keys as base64-encoded values\n116: - [ ] Create `jwt_test.go` with comprehensive tests\n117:   - [ ] `TestGenerateToken`\n118:   - [ ] `TestValidateToken`\n119:   - [ ] `TestTokenExpiration`\